  "text": "We estimate that around 245 000 people died in 2008 having had a diagnosis of cancer, of whom 64% died from their cancer and 36% died because of some other cause (see Figure 1 ; Information Services Division (ISD) Scotland, 2010; Northern Ireland Cancer Registry, 2011; Welsh Cancer Intelligence and Surveillance Unit, 2010; [CITATION_1] Office for National Statistics, 2010a ). This estimate is intended to be indicative only. Given the inaccuracies associated with death registrations and cause of death, more accurate estimates cannot be made (Office for National Statistics, 2010b) . The estimated proportions are consistent with similar data for South West England (South West Public Health Observatory, Cancer Intelligence Service, 2009) .",
