      "span_text": "We estimate that around 245 000 people died in 2008 having had a diagnosis of cancer, of whom 64% died from their cancer and 36% died because of some other cause (see Figure 1; Information Services Division (ISD) Scotland, 2010; Northern Ireland Cancer Registry, 2011; Welsh Cancer Intelligence and Surveillance Unit, 2010;"
